text: Jack Kehoe (November 21, 1934 - January 14, 2020) was an American actor. He was born in California. His best known roles were in Serpico (1973), The Pope of Greenwich Village (1984) and Brian De Palma's The Untouchables (1987), as well as the cult favorites Car Wash (1976) and Midnight Run (1988), the popular western Young Guns II (1990), and On the Nickel (1980). Kehoe died on January 14, 2020 from stroke-related problems in Los Angeles at the age of 85.Jack Kehoe, Actor in 'Serpico' and 'The Sting,' Dies at 85 ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1934 births Category:American movie actors Category:American television actors Category:American stage actors Category:Deaths from stroke Category:Actors from California Category:2020 deaths
